title: Boys soccer: South Brunswick gets top seed in GMC Tournament
text:
Boys soccer: South Brunswick gets top seed in GMC Tournament Daniel LoGiudice, @danny_logiudice 12:59 p.m. EDT October 16, 2015 32 CONNECT 6 TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
The 2015 Greater Middlesex Conference Boys Soccer Tournament has just been seeded with recent Red Divison champ South Brunswick earning the top seed for the second-straight season. 
Despite earning the top seed last season, South Brunswick fell to St. Joseph, which garnered the No. 5 seed, in the semifinal round. The Vikings, who just won their 500th game on Thursday, will look to make it all the way to the finals this year. 
The top eight seeds earned a double-bye into the first round. Seeds 9-17 earned a bye into the preliminary round. 
The play-in round is slated for next Tuesday, and the preliminary round is scheduled two days later on Thursday, Oct. 22. The quarterfinals are scheduled for Oct. 27, with the semifinals Oct. 29 and the final Saturday, Oct. 31. 
Here are the seeds and matchups: 
31-Perth Amboy Tech at 18-Perth Amboy, winner at 15-North Brunswick, winner at 2-New Brunswick; 30-Edison Academy at 19-Middlesex, winner at 14-South River, winner at 3- Monroe; 29-Woodbridge Academy at 20-Piscataway, winner at 13-Colonia, winner at 4-East Brunswick; 28-Piscataway Tech at 21-Edison, winner at 12-Bishop Ahr, winner at 5-St. Joseph; 27-Highland Park at 22-Wardlaw Hartridge, winner at 11-Sayreville, winner at 6-South Plainfield; 26-South Amboy at 23-J.F. Kennedy, winner at 10-Spotswood, winner at 7-Metuchen; 25-Woodbridge at 24-Timothy Christian, winner at 9-Old Bridge, winner at 8-East Brunswick Tech; 17-Carteret at 16-J.P.
